Step 1: Tech Stack Proposal

Given the scale and requirements:

Backend

Framework: Django (Python)

Reason: Robust, scalable, batteries-included, excellent for multi-role systems

Optional: Django REST Framework (DRF) for API endpoints (for frontend React to consume)

Database: PostgreSQL

Reason: Relational DBMS with strong support for complex queries, spatial/location queries (via PostGIS extension), scalability, and inventory management

Authentication/Authorization: Django’s built-in User model + custom roles

Roles: Consumer, Retailer, Wholesaler, Admin

Other Libraries:

Celery (for notifications, low inventory alerts)

Django Channels (if you want live updates, optional for now)

Frontend

Framework: React.js

Reason: You already know React; it’s perfect for dynamic, interactive interfaces

UI Libraries:

Tailwind CSS (fast styling)

Optional: Ant Design or Material UI for components like tables, modals, dashboards

Routing: React Router or TanStack Router (you already used this before)

Data Visualization:

Recharts or Chart.js (for admin/retailer dashboards, inventory visualization)

Other Considerations

Location-based filtering:

Use PostGIS in PostgreSQL for geo-queries

Or simple latitude/longitude fields + Haversine formula for distance calculations

Inventory Management Features:

Product quantity, expiry, shelf location, threshold alerts

Admin/retailer dashboard for visualization

Messaging / Support system:

Can start with a simple ticket system (open/close messages)

